methods.name: __construct

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The resource name of the job. Format: projects/{project_number}/locations/{location}/jobs/{job}

params.name: data.input_uri
params.description: Input only. Specify the input_uri to populate empty uri fields in each element of Job.config.inputs or JobTemplate.config.inputs when using template. URI of the media. Input files must be at least 5 seconds in duration and stored in Cloud Storage (for example, gs://bucket/inputs/file.mp4). See Supported input and output formats.

params.name: data.output_uri
params.description: Input only. Specify the output_uri to populate an empty Job.config.output.uri or JobTemplate.config.output.uri when using template. URI for the output file(s). For example, gs://my-bucket/outputs/. See Supported input and output formats.

params.name: data.template_id
params.description: Input only. Specify the template_id to use for populating Job.config. The default is preset/web-hd. Preset Transcoder templates: - preset/{preset_id} - User defined JobTemplate: {job_template_id}

params.name: data.config
params.description: The configuration for this job.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. The current state of the job.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. The time the job was created.

params.name: data.start_time
params.description: Output only. The time the transcoding started.

params.name: data.end_time
params.description: Output only. The time the transcoding finished.

params.name: data.ttl_after_completion_days
params.description: Job time to live value in days, which will be effective after job completion. Job should be deleted automatically after the given TTL. Enter a value between 1 and 90. The default is 30.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: The labels associated with this job. You can use these to organize and group your jobs.

params.name: data.error
params.description: Output only. An error object that describes the reason for the failure. This property is always present when state is FAILED.
